{
  "text": "A total of 100 \u03bcg mitochondrial protein was loaded on an 8-16% Tris/glycine/SDS gel (Bio-rad) and run at 100 V for 10 min, then 160 V for 1 h. The gel was stained with Coomassie blue R-250 (50% methanol, 10% acetic acid, 0.1% R-250) for 1 h and destained overnight in a solution containing 5% methanol/7% acetic acid. After imaging, stained protein bands were cut into 10 fractions according to molecular weight and distribution of protein abundance, and each fraction was then excised into smaller pieces of approximately 1 to 2 mm 3 . The gel pieces were destained with 50% methanol/5% acetic acid overnight, and in-gel digestion was performed as described previously [CITATION_1] . The extracted peptides were desalted with a reverse-phase (RP) Atlantis dC18 column (Waters, Milford, MA).",
  "correct_citation": {
